<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://w3id.org/perkonto/1.0.0> .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Debarshi Kumar Sanyal" .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Partha Pratim Das" .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Prantika Chakraborty" .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Srijoni Majumdar" .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A domain-specific ontology for representing the professional  knowledge of a researcher as extractable from personal email  communications. PERKOnto models communication infrastructure, researchers and venues, the publication lifecycle, and research content,  anchoring every assertion to its provenance email."@en .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "PERKOnto: Personal Email Research Knowledge Ontology"@en .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://github.com/prantikaC/PERK> .
<https://w3id.org/perkonto> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "1.0.0" .
